cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper proposes a method for viewpoint estimation using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for volume visualization. The paper focuses on designing an overfit-resistant image rendering pipeline and training a category-specific viewpoint classification network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Graphics (cs.GR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses how experts look at volumes, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a CNN feature-based image similarity measure for similarity voting based viewpoint selection, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
